# Third-Party Licenses

This document lists the open source software libraries used in the Nova Sonic Next.js + FastAPI Demo project and their respective licenses.

## Backend Dependencies (Python)

### FastAPI
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi
- **Description**: Modern, fast web framework for building APIs with Python

### Uvicorn
- **License**: BSD 3-Clause License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/encode/uvicorn
- **Description**: Lightning-fast ASGI server implementation

### WebSockets
- **License**: BSD 3-Clause License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/python-websockets/websockets
- **Description**: Library for building WebSocket servers and clients in Python

### Python-multipart
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/andrew-d/python-multipart
- **Description**: Streaming multipart parser for Python

### PyAudio
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/intxcc/pyaudio_portaudio
- **Description**: Python bindings for PortAudio, a cross-platform audio I/O library

### urllib3
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3
- **Description**: HTTP library with thread-safe connection pooling, file post, and more

### Smithy Core
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-python
- **Description**: Transport-agnostic core modules and interfaces for building service clients

### Smithy HTTP
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-python
- **Description**: HTTP core modules and interfaces for building HTTP service clients

### Smithy JSON
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-python
- **Description**: JSON serialization and deserialization for Smithy clients

### Smithy AWS Core
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-python
- **Description**: AWS-specific implementations of Smithy core interfaces

### Smithy AWS Event Stream
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-python
- **Description**: AWS Event Stream support for Smithy clients

## Frontend Dependencies (JavaScript/TypeScript)

### React
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/facebook/react
- **Description**: JavaScript library for building user interfaces

### Next.js
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/vercel/next.js
- **Description**: React framework for production applications

### Radix UI Components
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/radix-ui/primitives
- **Components Used**: Avatar, Separator, Slider, Slot
- **Description**: Low-level UI primitives and components

### Tailwind CSS
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss
- **Description**: Utility-first CSS framework

### Framer Motion
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/framer/motion
- **Description**: Production-ready motion library for React

### Lucide React
- **License**: ISC License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/lucide-icons/lucide
- **Description**: Beautiful & consistent icon toolkit

### TypeScript
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript
- **Description**: Typed superset of JavaScript

### Class Variance Authority (CVA)
- **License**: Apache License 2.0
- **Repository**: https://github.com/joe-bell/cva
- **Description**: Utility for creating type-safe component variants

### clsx
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/lukeed/clsx
- **Description**: Utility for constructing className strings conditionally

### Tailwind Merge
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/dcastil/tailwind-merge
- **Description**: Utility function to merge Tailwind CSS classes

## Development Dependencies

### ESLint
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/eslint/eslint
- **Description**: Tool for identifying and reporting on patterns in JavaScript

### PostCSS
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/postcss/postcss
- **Description**: Tool for transforming CSS with JavaScript

### tw-animate-css
- **License**: MIT License
- **Repository**: https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss-animate
- **Description**: Tailwind CSS plugin for animations

## License Types Summary

- **MIT License**: FastAPI, Uvicorn, PyAudio, urllib3, React, Next.js, Radix UI, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, clsx, Tailwind Merge, ESLint, PostCSS, tw-animate-css
- **BSD 3-Clause License**: Uvicorn, WebSockets
- **Apache License 2.0**: Python-multipart, TypeScript, Class Variance Authority, Smithy Core, Smithy HTTP, Smithy JSON, Smithy AWS Core, Smithy AWS Event Stream
- **ISC License**: Lucide React

## Notice

This project is a demonstration/sample application. All third-party libraries are used in accordance with their respective licenses. For complete license texts, please refer to the individual repositories listed above.

